        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3367984833" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10589008244065728412">An interesting and discordant read. The book is well-written, daring and controversial. Everything a classic should be. It explores themes of identity, colonialism and multiculturalism, and deploys them in typical symbolic mold which is apt to make the reader think and ponder about them. That being said, it leaves a bitter taste for it&apos;s over-the-top pontification of sexual exploits, to the point where it stops being part and of the story and starts to be a self-indulgent act.</span>
  <span id="freeText10589008244065728412" style="display:none">An interesting and discordant read. The book is well-written, daring and controversial. Everything a classic should be. It explores themes of identity, colonialism and multiculturalism, and deploys them in typical symbolic mold which is apt to make the reader think and ponder about them. That being said, it leaves a bitter taste for it's over-the-top pontification of sexual exploits, to the point where it stops being part and of the story and starts to be a self-indulgent act.</span>
